{
  "video_id": "SuUNnwswH94",
  "title": "Physic Materials - Unity Official Tutorials",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 2300.0,
      "text": "Physic Materials are materials that instead"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 2300.0,
      "end_time": 4300.0,
      "text": "of effecting the appearance of a game object"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 4300.0,
      "end_time": 6300.0,
      "text": "they effect the way that the object reacts"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 6300.0,
      "end_time": 8300.0,
      "text": "to the physics engine. Consider the difference"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 8300.0,
      "end_time": 10760.0,
      "text": "between how a basketball and a bowling ball"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 10760.0,
      "end_time": 12760.0,
      "text": "might bounce. Whilst there is a difference"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 12760.0,
      "end_time": 14760.0,
      "text": "in their mass, their surfaces are also"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 14760.0,
      "end_time": 17130.0,
      "text": "very different and they react to other"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 17130.0,
      "end_time": 19130.0,
      "text": "surfaces very differently. Physic materials"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 19130.0,
      "end_time": 21130.0,
      "text": "can be created from the Create button"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 21130.0,
      "end_time": 24890.0,
      "text": "on the project panel."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 24890.0,
      "end_time": 26890.0,
      "text": "And they&#39;re edited in the inspector to"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 26890.0,
      "end_time": 29030.0,
      "text": "control how the surface reacts to another"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 29030.0,
      "end_time": 31980.0,
      "text": "surface. They do this by controlling friction."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 31980.0,
      "end_time": 33980.0,
      "text": "Dynamic Friction is how much friction"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 33980.0,
      "end_time": 35980.0,
      "text": "exists whilst the object is moving"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 35980.0,
      "end_time": 38100.0,
      "text": "and Static Friction is how much"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 38100.0,
      "end_time": 40100.0,
      "text": "force is required in order to move the"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 40100.0,
      "end_time": 42020.0,
      "text": "object from a static position."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 42020.0,
      "end_time": 44260.0,
      "text": "Bounciness does exactly what it sounds like."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 44260.0,
      "end_time": 46870.0,
      "text": "It controls how bouncy the object is."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 46870.0,
      "end_time": 48950.0,
      "text": "And the Friction Combine settings control"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 48950.0,
      "end_time": 51780.0,
      "text": "how they respond to another object"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 51780.0,
      "end_time": 54290.0,
      "text": "with a certain material. Friction Direction"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 54290.0,
      "end_time": 56290.0,
      "text": "will allow you to control friction"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 56290.0,
      "end_time": 58780.0,
      "text": "in a particular axis and the dynamic"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 58780.0,
      "end_time": 60780.0,
      "text": "and static friction 2 properties"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 60780.0,
      "end_time": 63570.0,
      "text": "will give you control over those three axes."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 63570.0,
      "end_time": 66010.0,
      "text": "In this example we&#39;ve applied this"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 66010.0,
      "end_time": 68960.0,
      "text": "particular physic material to our power cube"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 68960.0,
      "end_time": 71720.0,
      "text": "and our work bench."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 71720.0,
      "end_time": 73720.0,
      "text": "The physic material is applied to the"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 73720.0,
      "end_time": 76080.0,
      "text": "collider in any given game object"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 76080.0,
      "end_time": 77910.0,
      "text": "and you can see that there&#39;s a slot for"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 77910.0,
      "end_time": 82820.0,
      "text": "material within the collider settings."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 82820.0,
      "end_time": 85320.0,
      "text": "You can see that if I press play,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 85320.0,
      "end_time": 89290.0,
      "text": "it bounces slightly and is also very slippery."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 89290.0,
      "end_time": 91290.0,
      "text": "This is because I&#39;ve used 0 for dynamic"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 91290.0,
      "end_time": 93870.0,
      "text": "and static friction, meaning there&#39;s nothing"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 93870.0,
      "end_time": 95870.0,
      "text": "stopping it from slipping around and"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 95870.0,
      "end_time": 98370.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve also made it slightly bouncy."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 98370.0,
      "end_time": 100870.0,
      "text": "If I make it very bouncy"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 100870.0,
      "end_time": 104560.0,
      "text": "then it&#39;s going to bounce off of the table."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 104560.0,
      "end_time": 106860.0,
      "text": "And for example if I wanted to restrict"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 106860.0,
      "end_time": 108860.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s movement in a particular axis"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 108860.0,
      "end_time": 110860.0,
      "text": "so I can see that the X axis is the direction"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 110860.0,
      "end_time": 113300.0,
      "text": "in which it&#39;s sliding, so what I could do"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 113300.0,
      "end_time": 115300.0,
      "text": "is go back to that material and I&#39;ll set"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 115300.0,
      "end_time": 117940.0,
      "text": "my friction direction of X to 1 and"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 117940.0,
      "end_time": 120940.0,
      "text": "increase the dynamic friction. I&#39;m going to turn"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 120940.0,
      "end_time": 123670.0,
      "text": "bounciness back down to a lower number"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 123670.0,
      "end_time": 127470.0,
      "text": "so that it doesn&#39;t bounce off the table."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 127470.0,
      "end_time": 129470.0,
      "text": "And you can see that it&#39;s slowing to a halt"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 129470.0,
      "end_time": 132330.0,
      "text": "because of the amount of friction involved there."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 132330.0,
      "end_time": 139610.0,
      "text": "So we could make that slightly lower"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 139610.0,
      "end_time": 148740.0,
      "text": "and you can see it begins to slide."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 148740.0,
      "end_time": 150130.0,
      "text": "So hopefully you can see that with"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 150130.0,
      "end_time": 152130.0,
      "text": "physic materials you can completely control"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 152130.0,
      "end_time": 153580.0,
      "text": "the surface of an object"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 153580.0,
      "end_time": 163580.0,
      "text": "and how it responds to others."
    }
  ]
}